casebody.head_matter:
W. F. FELL ET AL. v. W. E. FARREL ET AL.
APPEAL BY DEFENDANTS FROM THE COURT OF COMMON PLEAS NO. 1 OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY.
Argued April 8, 1890
Decided May 5, 1890.
Righter v. Farrel, ante, 482, followed.
Before Pakson, C. J., Sterrett, Williams, McCollum and Mitchell, JJ.
No. 200 January Term 1890, Sup. Ct.; court below, No. 777 September Term 1887, C. P. No. 1.
Tbe facts of tbis case were tbe same as the facts of Righter y. Farrel, ante, 482, except in tbe amount of tbe plaintiffs’ claim. Tbe instructions to tbe jury were to the same effect, and the assignments of error raised tbe same questions.
Mr. Charles L. Smith (with him Mr. 'J. M. West), for the appellants.
Mr. Richard P. White, for tbe appellees.
